<a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=499762391&t=artid%3dd2110885-1416-4853-bbdb-8a9fe2e93a71%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" target="_blank"><img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=499762391&t=artid%3dd2110885-1416-4853-bbdb-8a9fe2e93a71%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" border="0" alt=""></a>It includes representatives of the family, the ANC Gauteng branch, community safety MEC Sizakele Nkosi-Malobane and sports, arts, culture and recreation MEC Faith Mazibuko, amongst others.Deputy president Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the eulogy on behalf of the presidency. Bra Willie will be buried at West Park Cemetery.“Kgositsile was among the pantheon of selfless men and women who courageously fought against apartheid and for the freedom of the people of South Africa,” said Langa.A memorial service was held on 6 January at the Modern Language Association building in New York.“The event included tributes by various activists who either knew Kgositsile personally or have been touched by his life.“In a true Kgositsile form, many of the commemorative events include the reading of poetry, jazz music and reflections on society. This is how Kgositsile would have preferred to be celebrated,” he said.Langa said that sessions to celebrate the life of Bra Willie are being held every day at the family home in Killarney.Condolence books will be made available at the family home and at the memorial services.Memorial services will be held at the Market Theatre in Newtown on 11 January and the Joburg City Hall on 12 January.
